==Japanese==

=== Etymology ===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[月]] || [[曜]] || [[日]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
From Latin ''[[dies lunae]]'' ("moon's day") through Indian astrology in the fifth century as Sanskrit ''somāha'', "moon-day" (''soma'', "moon") into Buddhist astrology in the 8th century as 月曜日: [[月]] (げつ, ''getsu'', "moon") + [[曜日]] (ようび, ''yōbi'', "day of the week").

===Noun===
{{janoun|げつようび|getsuyōbi}}
# [[Monday]]

===Synonyms===
*[[月曜]]

